---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import CTA from '../components/sections/CTA.astro';
---

<PageLayout
  title="For Travel Management Companies"
  description="Cinturon360 is built TMC-first. Replace Tramada and legacy mid-office tools with a modern platform for client management, automation, policy, integrations, and finance-grade reporting."
>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section
    class="relative overflow-hidden pt-32 pb-24 md:pt-40 md:pb-32"
    style="background: linear-gradient(30deg, #38bdf833 0%, #0f172a 60%);"
  >
    <div class="absolute -top-20 -left-20 w-96 h-96 rounded-full opacity-20 blur-3xl pointer-events-none" style="background: #38bdf8;"></div>
    <div class="absolute top-40 right-0 w-72 h-72 rounded-full opacity-10 blur-3xl pointer-events-none" style="background: #f97316;"></div>

    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 max-w-7xl relative">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
        <div class="flex justify-center mb-8">
          <span class="hero-badge">
            <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-sky-400 animate-pulse"></span>
            Built for TMCs
          </span>
        </div>
        <h1 class="font-heading text-4xl md:text-6xl font-bold text-white mb-6 leading-tight">
          Built for how TMCs actually operate.
        </h1>
        <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-slate-300 mb-4 max-w-3xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
          Cinturon360 is a TMC-first platform that replaces legacy back-office complexity with modern automation, governance, and visibility — without disrupting your existing booking channels or supplier relationships.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mb-10">
          Replaces Tramada. Works alongside GDS, NDC, and direct suppliers. No rip-and-replace.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-center gap-4">
          <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary text-base px-8 py-4">
            Book a Conversation
          </a>
          <a href="/waitlist" class="btn-outline text-base px-8 py-4">
            Join Waitlist
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pain points -->
  <section class="section bg-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 max-w-7xl">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-medium bg-orange-100 text-orange-700 mb-4">
          The problem
        </span>
        <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">
          What a TMC's day looks like without Cinturon360
        </h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
          Legacy tools were built for a different era. The gap between what TMCs need and what their software delivers has never been wider.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        {[
          {
            title: 'Manual client onboarding',
            body: 'Every new client means another bespoke spreadsheet, manual setup, and phone calls. No repeatable process. No scalable playbook.',
          },
          {
            title: 'Approvals stuck in email',
            body: 'Travel gets booked before anyone approves it. Finance only finds out at invoice time. There\'s no system of record for who approved what.',
          },
          {
            title: 'Reporting built in Excel',
            body: 'Someone spends two days each month compiling a spend report that\'s already out of date by the time it reaches the client.',
          },
          {
            title: 'Policy enforcement is theoretical',
            body: 'The policy document exists. Nobody follows it consistently. There\'s no way to prove compliance to a client or regulator.',
          },
          {
            title: 'Integration is a project, not a feature',
            body: 'Connecting a new GDS, NDC feed, or supplier requires custom development. Every client configuration is different and fragile.',
          },
          {
            title: 'Scaling means hiring, not automating',
            body: 'As client volume grows, headcount grows with it. There\'s no platform leverage — just more people doing the same manual work.',
          },
        ].map((item) => (
          <div class="rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-100 bg-slate-50">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-2 h-2 rounded-full mt-2 bg-orange-400"></span>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-heading font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2">{item.title}</h3>
                <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">{item.body}</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What Cinturon360 delivers -->
  <section class="section bg-slate-50">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 max-w-7xl">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-medium bg-sky-100 text-sky-700 mb-4">
          Platform capabilities
        </span>
        <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">
          What TMCs get with Cinturon360
        </h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
          Not a point solution for one problem. A platform that handles the operations layer so your team can focus on clients, not administration.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        {[
          {
            icon: '⚙️',
            title: 'Automated client onboarding',
            body: 'Repeatable, configurable onboarding workflows for every new corporate client. Policy rules, approval chains, cost centre mapping, and reporting templates — set up once, deployed consistently.',
            link: '/platform/tmc-operations',
          },
          {
            icon: '🛡️',
            title: 'Policy and approval engine',
            body: 'Define rules by entity, traveller, cost centre, destination, supplier, fare cap, or exception type. Route to the right approvers before spend is committed. Full audit trail, always.',
            link: '/platform/policy-approvals',
          },
          {
            icon: '🔗',
            title: 'Integration layer — no rip-and-replace',
            body: 'Cinturon360 connects to GDS (Amadeus, Sabre, Travelport), NDC feeds (Duffel, AirGateway), and direct suppliers. Your booking channels stay exactly where they are.',
            link: '/platform/integrations',
          },
          {
            icon: '📊',
            title: 'Finance-grade reporting',
            body: 'Real-time spend visibility by client, cost centre, segment, and traveller. Compliance reporting ready for client review, internal audit, or board presentation.',
            link: '/platform/reporting-visibility',
          },
          {
            icon: '🔄',
            title: 'Mid-office workflow automation',
            body: 'Booking intake, quality control, exception handling, and client notifications — all automated. Replace manual mid-office tasks with configurable workflow logic.',
            link: '/platform/tmc-operations',
          },
          {
            icon: '📈',
            title: 'Scale without headcount',
            body: 'Take on more clients without proportionally growing your ops team. Platform leverage means the work done for one client configuration lifts every client that follows.',
            link: '/platform/performance-scale',
          },
        ].map((item) => (
          <div class="card flex flex-col group">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-sky-50 flex items-center justify-center text-xl mb-4">{item.icon}</div>
            <h3 class="font-heading text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">{item.title}</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed flex-1 mb-4">{item.body}</p>
            <a href={item.link} class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-sm font-medium text-sky-600 hover:text-sky-700 transition-colors mt-auto">
              Learn more
              <svg class="w-4 h-4 transition-transform group-hover:translate-x-0.5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7" />
              </svg>
            </a>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Tramada replacement -->
  <section class="section" style="background: #0f172a;">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 max-w-7xl">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <div class="text-center mb-12">
          <span class="inline-flex items-center px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-medium mb-4"
            style="background: rgba(249,115,22,0.15); color: #f97316;">
            Tramada alternative
          </span>
          <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-4">
            A modern replacement for legacy mid-office
          </h2>
          <p class="text-slate-400 text-lg leading-relaxed">
            Tramada has served the industry well. But it was built for a different era — before NDC, before cloud-native platforms, before the modern compliance bar. Cinturon360 is what comes next.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-10">
          <div class="rounded-xl p-6" style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.04); border: 1px solid rgba(249,115,22,0.2);">
            <h3 class="font-heading font-semibold text-orange-400 mb-4">Legacy mid-office (Tramada)</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-3">
              {[
                'On-premise or dated cloud infrastructure',
                'Manual configuration for each client',
                'Limited NDC and modern supplier connectivity',
                'Reporting requires custom exports and Excel',
                'Expensive to customise, slow to update',
                'Approval workflows bolted on or absent',
              ].map((item) => (
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-slate-400">
                  <svg class="w-4 h-4 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5 text-slate-600" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12" />
                  </svg>
                  {item}
                </li>
              ))}
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-xl p-6" style="background: rgba(56,189,248,0.06); border: 1px solid rgba(56,189,248,0.2);">
            <h3 class="font-heading font-semibold text-sky-400 mb-4">Cinturon360</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-3">
              {[
                'Cloud-native, APAC-hosted, globally scalable',
                'Repeatable client onboarding via configuration',
                'Native GDS, NDC, and direct supplier connectivity',
                'Real-time reporting, no exports required',
                'API-first, continuously updated',
                'Approval workflows built into the core data model',
              ].map((item) => (
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-slate-300">
                  <svg class="w-4 h-4 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5 text-sky-400" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
                  </svg>
                  {item}
                </li>
              ))}
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p class="text-center text-slate-500 text-sm">
          Migration support and parallel-run capability available for TMCs transitioning from Tramada.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Integrations -->
  <section class="section bg-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 max-w-7xl">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-medium bg-purple-100 text-purple-700 mb-4">
          Integrations
        </span>
        <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">
          Works with the ecosystem you already use
        </h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
          No forced migrations. Cinturon360 connects to your existing GDS, NDC, and supplier relationships — adding governance and visibility on top of what's already working.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-4 mb-8">
        {[
          { name: 'Amadeus', type: 'GDS' },
          { name: 'Sabre', type: 'GDS' },
          { name: 'Travelport', type: 'GDS' },
          { name: 'Duffel', type: 'NDC' },
          { name: 'AirGateway', type: 'NDC' },
          { name: 'Direct Suppliers', type: 'API' },
          { name: 'Expense Platforms', type: 'ERP' },
          { name: 'Custom Connectors', type: 'API' },
        ].map((item) => (
          <div class="rounded-xl p-4 text-center border border-slate-100 bg-slate-50">
            <p class="font-semibold text-slate-800 text-sm">{item.name}</p>
            <span class="inline-flex items-center px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full text-xs bg-slate-200 text-slate-600 mt-1">{item.type}</span>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <div class="text-center">
        <a href="/platform/integrations" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-medium text-sky-600 hover:text-sky-700 transition-colors">
          View full integrations documentation
          <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7" />
          </svg>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pricing note -->
  <section class="section bg-slate-50">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 max-w-7xl">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">
          Pricing built around your operation
        </h2>
        <p class="text-slate-600 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
          No two TMCs operate the same way. Cinturon360 pricing is a custom model built around your client volume, workflow complexity, and commercial requirements. There's no off-the-shelf tier that fits a TMC operation — so we don't pretend there is.
        </p>
        <a href="/pricing" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-medium text-sky-600 hover:text-sky-700 transition-colors">
          How pricing works →
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTA
    title="Ready to modernise your TMC operations?"
    description="Join the waitlist or book a conversation with the team. We're working with early design partners now — TMCs that want to shape the platform."
    primaryCTA={{ label: 'Book a Conversation', href: '/contact' }}
    secondaryCTA={{ label: 'Join Waitlist', href: '/waitlist' }}
  />

</PageLayout>
